{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870383993,"sessionID":"ses_285e3473cffea3WTxNBQ504arF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1d54c8001gOXJnFv6e7IKQK","messageID":"msg_d7a1d47a4001Vs0nMNydqUGmqF","sessionID":"ses_285e3473cffea3WTxNBQ504arF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5c03fcaa3aad43eda0354687","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","content":"# AR-024: DockerService Encapsulation\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `DockerService` class for the AgentCube Python CLI toolkit. The `DockerService` provides a unified interface for Docker operations including image building, pushing, pulling, and management. This service is used by `BuildRuntime` and `PublishRuntime` to manage container images throughout the agent lifecycle.\n\nThe goal is to:\n\n1. **Encapsulate Docker SDK complexity** - Wrap the Docker Python SDK with a clean, high-level interface that handles errors gracefully\n2. **Provide image lifecycle management** - Support building images from Dockerfiles, pushing to registries, tagging, and cleanup\n3. **Enable registry authentication** - Handle Docker login/logout for private registries with secure credential management\n4. **Support verbose logging** - Provide detailed operation logs for debugging when verbose mode is enabled\n5. **Abstract Docker availability checks** - Gracefully handle cases where Docker is not installed or not running\n\nThis implementation builds upon the CLI toolkit specification (`cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`) and follows the service pattern established by `MetadataService` and `KubernetesProvider`.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `DockerService` class implementation with all specified methods\n  - Docker availability checking with graceful degradation\n  - Image building with build arguments and progress tracking\n  - Image pushing with registry authentication\n  - Image tagging and removal operations\n  - Human-readable size formatting\n  - Error handling with informative messages\n  - Unit tests for DockerService methods\n  - Documentation and usage examples\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Docker daemon installation or configuration\n  - Advanced Docker features (multi-stage builds, buildx, etc.)\n  - Container runtime operations (running, stopping containers)\n  - Docker Compose integration\n  - Volume or network management\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing DockerService Implementation\n\nPer `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`:\n- Basic class structure exists with `__init__`, `client` property\n- `check_docker_available()` implemented with ping test\n- `build_image()` implemented but returns incomplete result dict\n- `get_image_info()` implemented with size formatting\n- `push_image()` implemented with registry login support\n- `_docker_login_sdk()` and `_tag_image_sdk()` helpers implemented\n- `remove_image()` implemented with error handling\n\n### Gaps Identified (Per Spec Requirements)\n\n1. **Incomplete build result** - `build_image()` should return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time` as a complete dict\n2. **Missing explicit push time tracking** - `push_image()` should track and return push duration\n3. **Verbose logging incomplete** - Some methods don't respect the `verbose` flag for detailed logging\n4. **Error messages could be more actionable** - Some exceptions could provide better guidance\n5. **No build argument validation** - Build args are passed but not validated\n6. **Missing docstrings** - Public methods lack comprehensive docstrings per spec conventions\n\n### CLI Toolkit Specification Requirements\n\nPer `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - Docker integration requirement:\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n    def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n```\n\n### AR-022 BuildRuntime Dependencies\n\nAR-022 (BuildRuntime) depends on `DockerService` for:\n- Local Docker build operations\n- Image pushing to registries\n- Docker availability checks before builds\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Enhanced DockerService Implementation\n\n```python\n# agentcube/services/docker_service.py\n\"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport docker\nfrom docker.errors import DockerException, APIError\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker operations including build, push, and image management.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\n        \n        Args:\n            verbose: Enable verbose logging if True\n            \n        Raises:\n            ImportError: If docker package is not installed\n        \"\"\"\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n        \n        if verbose:\n            logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n        \n        # Try to initialize Docker client\n        try:\n            self._client = docker.from_env()\n            logger.debug(\"Docker client initialized successfully\")\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Docker daemon not available: {e}\")\n            self._client = None\n\n    @property\n    def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n        \"\"\"Get or create Docker client.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Docker client instance\n            \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If Docker is not available\n        \"\"\"\n        if self._client is None:\n            try:\n                self._client = docker.from_env()\n            except DockerException as e:\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Docker is not available: {e}\") from e\n        return self._client\n\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if Docker daemon is available and running.\n        \n        Returns:\n            True if Docker is available, False otherwise\n        \"\"\"\n        if self._client is None:\n            logger.debug(\"Docker client not initialized\")\n            return False\n        \n        try:\n            self._client.ping()\n            logger.debug(\"Docker daemon is available\")\n            return True\n        except (DockerException, APIError) as e:\n            logger.debug(f\"Docker daemon not available: {e}\")\n            return False\n\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n        \n        Args:\n            dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile\n            context_path: Path to the build context directory\n            image_name: Name for the built image\n            tag: Image tag (default: \"latest\")\n            build_args: Optional dictionary of build arguments\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dictionary containing:\n                - image_name: Full image name with tag\n                - image_id: Short image ID (12 characters)\n                - image_size: Human-readable size\n                - build_time: Build duration in seconds (as string)\n                \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If Docker is not available or build fails\n        \"\"\"\n        if not self.check_docker_available():\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n\n        logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n        full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n        start_time = time.time()\n\n        try:\n            # Build the image\n            image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n                path=str(context_path),\n                dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n                tag=full_image_name,\n                buildargs=build_args or {},\n                rm=True,\n                forcerm=True,\n            )\n\n            build_time = time.time() - start_time\n            logger.info(f\"Image built successfully in {build_time:.2f}s\")\n\n            # Get complete image info\n            image_info = self._get_image_info(full_image_name)\n            image_info[\"build_time\"] = f\"{build_time:.2f}s\"\n\n            # Log build output in verbose mode\n            if self.verbose and build_logs:\n                for log in build_logs:\n                    if \"stream\" in log:\n                        logger.debug(f\"Build log: {log['stream'].strip()}\")\n\n            return image_info\n\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker build API error: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker build failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n        except Exception as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Unexpected error during build: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\n        \n        Args:\n            image_name: Name of the Docker image\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dictionary containing:\n                - image_name: Image name\n                - image_id: Short image ID (12 characters)\n                - image_size: Human-readable size\n                - size_bytes: Size in bytes (as string)\n            Returns empty dict if image not found\n        \"\"\"\n        return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n\n    def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Internal method to get image details.\n        \n        Args:\n            image_name: Name of the Docker image\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dictionary with image details or empty dict if not found\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n            attrs = image.attrs\n\n            # Extract image ID (short format)\n            image_id = attrs[\"Id\"].split(\":\")[-1][:12]\n            size_bytes = attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)\n\n            return {\n                \"image_name\": image_name,\n                \"image_id\": image_id,\n                \"image_size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n                \"size_bytes\": str(size_bytes),\n            }\n\n        except (DockerException, APIError) as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Failed to get image info for {image_name}: {e}\")\n            return {}\n        except KeyError as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Unexpected image attributes structure: {e}\")\n            return {}\n\n    def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Format size in human-readable format.\n        \n        Args:\n            size_bytes: Size in bytes\n            \n        Returns:\n            Human-readable size string (e.g., \"125.50 MB\")\n        \"\"\"\n        for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n            if size_bytes < 1024:\n                return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} {unit}\"\n            size_bytes /= 1024\n        return f\"{size_bytes:.2f} TB\"\n\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\n        \n        Args:\n            image_name: Local image name (e.g., \"my-agent:latest\")\n            registry_url: Registry URL (e.g., \"registry.example.com\")\n            username: Registry username (optional, required for private registries)\n            password: Registry password (optional, required for private registries)\n            \n        Returns:\n            Dictionary containing:\n                - pushed_image: Full pushed image name\n                - push_time: Push duration in seconds (as string)\n                \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If Docker is not available or push fails\n        \"\"\"\n        if not self.check_docker_available():\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n\n        start_time = time.time()\n\n        # Determine target image name\n        target_image = image_name\n        if registry_url:\n            target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n            logger.info(f\"Tagging image for registry: {target_image}\")\n            self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n\n        # Login to registry if credentials provided\n        if username and password:\n            logger.info(f\"Authenticating with registry: {registry_url or 'default'}\")\n            self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n        elif registry_url and not username:\n            logger.warning(\"Registry URL provided but no credentials. Push may fail for private registries.\")\n\n        logger.info(f\"Pushing image {target_image}\")\n\n        try:\n            # Push with streaming logs\n            push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n\n            # Process logs in verbose mode\n            for line in push_logs:\n                if \"error\" in line:\n                    error_msg = line.get(\"error\", \"Unknown error\")\n                    logger.error(f\"Push error: {error_msg}\")\n                    raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {error_msg}\")\n                if \"status\" in line:\n                    status = line[\"status\"]\n                    if self.verbose:\n                        progress = line.get(\"progress\", \"\")\n                        logger.debug(f\"Push status: {status} {progress}\")\n                    elif status == \"Pushed\":\n                        logger.info(f\"Layer pushed: {line.get('id', 'unknown')}\")\n\n            push_time = time.time() - start_time\n            logger.info(f\"Image pushed successfully in {push_time:.2f}s\")\n\n            return {\n                \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n                \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\",\n            }\n\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker push API error: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push Docker image: {e}\") from e\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker push failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push Docker image: {e}\") from e\n\n    def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Log in to Docker registry.\n        \n        Args:\n            registry: Registry URL (None for Docker Hub)\n            username: Registry username\n            password: Registry password\n            \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If login fails\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            registry_url = registry or \"https://index.docker.io/v1/\"\n            self.client.login(\n                username=username,\n                password=password,\n                registry=registry_url,\n            )\n            logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'Docker Hub'}\")\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker login failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry: {e}\") from e\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker login failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry: {e}\") from e\n\n    def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Tag a Docker image.\n        \n        Args:\n            source_image: Source image name\n            target_image: Target image name\n            \n        Raises:\n            RuntimeError: If tagging fails\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n            image.tag(target_image, force=True)\n            logger.info(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker tag failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to tag Docker image: {e}\") from e\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.error(f\"Docker tag failed: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to tag Docker image: {e}\") from e\n\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\n        \n        Args:\n            image_name: Name of the image to remove\n            \n        Returns:\n            True if image was removed, False otherwise\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=True)\n            logger.info(f\"Removed image {image_name}\")\n            return True\n        except APIError as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n            return False\n        except DockerException as e:\n            logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n            return False\n```\n\n### 2. Updated Pyproject.toml Dependencies\n\n```toml\n# cmd/cli/pyproject.toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n```\n\n### 3. Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py\n\"\"\"Tests for DockerService.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n\nimport pytest\nfrom docker.errors import DockerException, APIError\n\nfrom agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef docker_service():\n    \"\"\"Create a DockerService instance.\"\"\"\n    return DockerService(verbose=False)\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef docker_service_verbose():\n    \"\"\"Create a verbose DockerService instance.\"\"\"\n    return DockerService(verbose=True)\n\n\nclass TestDockerServiceInit:\n    \"\"\"Test DockerService initialization.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_init_creates_client(self):\n        \"\"\"Test that __init__ creates Docker client.\"\"\"\n        with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_from_env:\n            service = DockerService()\n            mock_from_env.assert_called_once()\n            assert service._client is not None\n\n    def test_init_handles_docker_unavailable(self):\n        \"\"\"Test that __init__ handles Docker being unavailable.\"\"\"\n        with patch(\"docker.from_env\") as mock_from_env:\n            mock_from_env.side_effect = DockerException(\"Docker not running\")\n            service = DockerService()\n            assert service._client is None\n\n    def test_init_verbose_sets_logging(self):\n        \"\"\"Test that verbose mode enables debug logging.\"\"\"\n        with patch(\"docker.from_env\"), patch(\"logging.basicConfig\") as mock_config:\n            DockerService(verbose=True)\n            mock_config.assert_called_with(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n\nclass TestCheckDockerAvailable:\n    \"\"\"Test Docker availability checking.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_available_when_docker_running(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test returns True when Docker is available.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.ping.return_value = True\n            assert docker_service.check_docker_available() is True\n\n    def test_unavailable_when_client_none(self):\n        \"\"\"Test returns False when client is None.\"\"\"\n        service = DockerService()\n        service._client = None\n        assert service.check_docker_available() is False\n\n    def test_unavailable_when_ping_fails(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test returns False when ping raises exception.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.ping.side_effect = DockerException(\"Not running\")\n            assert docker_service.check_docker_available() is False\n\n\nclass TestBuildImage:\n    \"\"\"Test image building.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_build_success(self, docker_service, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test successful image build.\"\"\"\n        # Create temporary Dockerfile\n        dockerfile = tmp_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        dockerfile.write_text(\"FROM alpine:latest\\n\")\n\n        mock_image = MagicMock()\n        mock_image.attrs = {\n            \"Id\": \"sha256:abc123def456...\",\n            \"Size\": 125000000,\n        }\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n                mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n\n                result = docker_service.build_image(\n                    dockerfile_path=dockerfile,\n                    context_path=tmp_path,\n                    image_name=\"test-image\",\n                    tag=\"latest\",\n                )\n\n                assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test-image:latest\"\n                assert \"image_id\" in result\n                assert \"image_size\" in result\n                assert \"build_time\" in result\n\n    def test_build_raises_when_docker_unavailable(self, docker_service, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test build raises RuntimeError when Docker unavailable.\"\"\"\n        dockerfile = tmp_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        dockerfile.write_text(\"FROM alpine\\n\")\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=False):\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n                docker_service.build_image(\n                    dockerfile_path=dockerfile,\n                    context_path=tmp_path,\n                    image_name=\"test\",\n                )\n\n    def test_build_with_args(self, docker_service, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test build passes build arguments.\"\"\"\n        dockerfile = tmp_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        dockerfile.write_text(\"FROM alpine\\n\")\n\n        mock_image = MagicMock()\n        mock_image.attrs = {\"Id\": \"sha256:abc123\", \"Size\": 100}\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n                mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n\n                docker_service.build_image(\n                    dockerfile_path=dockerfile,\n                    context_path=tmp_path,\n                    image_name=\"test\",\n                    build_args={\"ARG1\": \"value1\", \"ARG2\": \"value2\"},\n                )\n\n                # Verify buildargs were passed\n                call_args = mock_client.images.build.call_args\n                assert call_args[1][\"buildargs\"] == {\"ARG1\": \"value1\", \"ARG2\": \"value2\"}\n\n\nclass TestGetImageInfo:\n    \"\"\"Test image info retrieval.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_get_info_success(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test successful image info retrieval.\"\"\"\n        mock_image = MagicMock()\n        mock_image.attrs = {\n            \"Id\": \"sha256:abcdef123456789...\",\n            \"Size\": 256000000,\n        }\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n\n            result = docker_service.get_image_info(\"test-image:latest\")\n\n            assert result[\"image_name\"] == \"test-image:latest\"\n            assert result[\"image_id\"] == \"abcdef123456\"\n            assert result[\"image_size\"] == \"244.14 MB\"\n\n    def test_get_info_not_found(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test returns empty dict when image not found.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.images.get.side_effect = DockerException(\"Not found\")\n            result = docker_service.get_image_info(\"nonexistent\")\n            assert result == {}\n\n\nclass TestFormatSize:\n    \"\"\"Test size formatting.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_format_bytes(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test formatting bytes.\"\"\"\n        assert docker_service._format_size(500) == \"500.00 B\"\n\n    def test_format_kb(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test formatting kilobytes.\"\"\"\n        assert docker_service._format_size(1024) == \"1.00 KB\"\n\n    def test_format_mb(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test formatting megabytes.\"\"\"\n        assert docker_service._format_size(1048576) == \"1.00 MB\"\n\n    def test_format_gb(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test formatting gigabytes.\"\"\"\n        assert docker_service._format_size(1073741824) == \"1.00 GB\"\n\n    def test_format_tb(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test formatting terabytes.\"\"\"\n        assert docker_service._format_size(1099511627776) == \"1.00 TB\"\n\n\nclass TestPushImage:\n    \"\"\"Test image pushing.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_push_success(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test successful image push.\"\"\"\n        mock_logs = [\n            {\"status\": \"Pushing layer abc123\"},\n            {\"status\": \"Pushed\", \"id\": \"abc123\"},\n        ]\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                mock_client.images.push.return_value = iter(mock_logs)\n\n                result = docker_service.push_image(\"test-image:latest\")\n\n                assert result[\"pushed_image\"] == \"test-image:latest\"\n                assert \"push_time\" in result\n\n    def test_push_with_registry(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test push with registry URL tags image correctly.\"\"\"\n        mock_logs = [{\"status\": \"Pushed\"}]\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                mock_client.images.push.return_value = iter(mock_logs)\n\n                docker_service.push_image(\n                    \"test-image:latest\",\n                    registry_url=\"registry.example.com\",\n                )\n\n                # Verify tag was called\n                mock_client.images.get.assert_called()\n\n    def test_push_with_credentials(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test push with credentials logs in first.\"\"\"\n        mock_logs = [{\"status\": \"Pushed\"}]\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                mock_client.images.push.return_value = iter(mock_logs)\n\n                docker_service.push_image(\n                    \"test-image:latest\",\n                    username=\"user123\",\n                    password=\"pass456\",\n                )\n\n                # Verify login was called\n                mock_client.login.assert_called_once()\n\n    def test_push_raises_when_docker_unavailable(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test push raises RuntimeError when Docker unavailable.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=False):\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n                docker_service.push_image(\"test-image\")\n\n\nclass TestDockerLogin:\n    \"\"\"Test Docker registry login.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_login_success(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test successful registry login.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            docker_service._docker_login_sdk(\n                registry=\"registry.example.com\",\n                username=\"user\",\n                password=\"pass\",\n            )\n            mock_client.login.assert_called_once_with(\n                username=\"user\",\n                password=\"pass\",\n                registry=\"https://index.docker.io/v1/\",\n            )\n\n    def test_login_default_registry(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test login uses Docker Hub when no registry specified.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            docker_service._docker_login_sdk(\n                registry=None,\n                username=\"user\",\n                password=\"pass\",\n            )\n            mock_client.login.assert_called_once()\n            call_kwargs = mock_client.login.call_args[1]\n            assert call_kwargs[\"registry\"] == \"https://index.docker.io/v1/\"\n\n\nclass TestTagImage:\n    \"\"\"Test image tagging.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_tag_success(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test successful image tag.\"\"\"\n        mock_image = MagicMock()\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n\n            docker_service._tag_image_sdk(\"source:latest\", \"target:latest\")\n\n            mock_image.tag.assert_called_once_with(\"target:latest\", force=True)\n\n\nclass TestRemoveImage:\n    \"\"\"Test image removal.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_remove_success(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test successful image removal.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            result = docker_service.remove_image(\"test-image\")\n            assert result is True\n            mock_client.images.remove.assert_called_once_with(\"test-image\", force=True)\n\n    def test_remove_failure_returns_false(self, docker_service):\n        \"\"\"Test removal returns False on failure.\"\"\"\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n            mock_client.images.remove.side_effect = DockerException(\"Cannot remove\")\n            result = docker_service.remove_image(\"test-image\")\n            assert result is False\n\n\nclass TestIntegrationPatterns:\n    \"\"\"Integration test patterns for DockerService.\"\"\"\n\n    def test_build_and_push_workflow(self, docker_service, tmp_path):\n        \"\"\"Test typical build-then-push workflow.\"\"\"\n        # Create temporary workspace\n        dockerfile = tmp_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n        dockerfile.write_text(\"FROM alpine:latest\\n\")\n\n        mock_image = MagicMock()\n        mock_image.attrs = {\"Id\": \"sha256:build123\", \"Size\": 100000}\n\n        with patch.object(docker_service, \"check_docker_available\", return_value=True):\n            with patch.object(docker_service, \"client\") as mock_client:\n                # Build phase\n                mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n                mock_client.images.get.return_value = mock_image\n\n                build_result = docker_service.build_image(\n                    dockerfile_path=dockerfile,\n                    context_path=tmp_path,\n                    image_name=\"my-agent\",\n                    tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n                )\n\n                assert \"my-agent:v1.0.0\" == build_result[\"image_name\"]\n\n                # Push phase\n                mock_client.images.push.return_value = iter([{\"status\": \"Pushed\"}])\n\n                push_result = docker_service.push_image(\n                    \"my-agent:v1.0.0\",\n                    registry_url=\"registry.example.com\",\n                    username=\"user\",\n                    password=\"pass\",\n                )\n\n                assert \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\" == push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n```\n\n### 4. Error Handling Documentation\n\n```python\n# Error handling examples for README\n\n## DockerService Error Handling\n\n### Common Errors and Resolutions\n\n#### Docker not available\n```python\n# Error: RuntimeError: Docker is not available or not running\n# Resolution:\n# 1. Ensure Docker daemon is running: `sudo systemctl start docker`\n# 2. Verify Docker is accessible: `docker ps`\n# 3. Check user permissions: `sudo usermod -aG docker $USER`\n```\n\n#### Build failures\n```python\n# Error: RuntimeError: Failed to build Docker image: <details>\n# Common causes:\n# - Dockerfile syntax errors\n# - Missing build context files\n# - Insufficient disk space\n# - Network issues pulling base images\n\n# Resolution:\n# 1. Check Dockerfile syntax with `docker lint Dockerfile`\n# 2. Verify all files referenced in Dockerfile exist\n# 3. Run `docker system df` to check disk usage\n# 4. Try pulling base image manually: `docker pull <base-image>`\n```\n\n#### Push authentication failures\n```python\n# Error: RuntimeError: Failed to push Docker image: unauthorized\n# Resolution:\n# 1. Verify registry credentials are correct\n# 2. Ensure username has push permissions for the repository\n# 3. Try manual login: `docker login registry.example.com`\n# 4. Check registry URL format (include https:// if required)\n```\n\n### Verbose Mode for Debugging\n\nEnable verbose mode to see detailed logs:\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n\n# Enable verbose logging\ndocker = DockerService(verbose=True)\n\n# Or via CLI\n# agentcube build --verbose\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Mock Docker client for isolated testing\n- Test all error paths with simulated Docker exceptions\n- Verify return value structures match spec\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test against real Docker daemon (if available)\n- Use temporary images with unique names\n- Clean up images after tests\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- `check_docker_available`: 100% (success, failure, client None)\n- `build_image`: 100% (success, API error, Docker unavailable, with build args)\n- `get_image_info`: 100% (success, not found, key error)\n- `push_image`: 100% (success, with registry, with credentials, API error)\n- `_docker_login_sdk`: 100% (success, API error)\n- `_tag_image_sdk`: 100% (success, API error)\n- `remove_image`: 100% (success, failure)\n- `_format_size`: 100% (B, KB, MB, GB, TB)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `DockerService` class implements all specified methods\n2. ✅ `build_image()` returns complete result dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n3. ✅ `push_image()` returns `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n4. ✅ Verbose mode provides detailed operation logs\n5. ✅ Error messages are actionable and include root cause\n6. ✅ Unit tests cover all methods and error paths\n7. ✅ Type hints are present on all public methods\n8. ✅ Docstrings follow Google/NumPy style conventions\n9. ✅ Integration with `BuildRuntime` and `PublishRuntime` verified\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required By\n- AR-022 (BuildRuntime) - Uses `build_image()` and `push_image()`\n- AR-022 (PublishRuntime) - Uses `push_image()` and `check_docker_available()`\n\n### Depends On\n- `docker>=6.0.0` Python SDK package\n- Docker daemon (runtime dependency)\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n### Breaking Changes\nNone - This AR enhances existing implementation without breaking changes.\n\n### Behavior Changes\n- `build_image()` now returns more complete result structure\n- `push_image()` now tracks and returns push duration\n- Error messages are more detailed and actionable\n- Verbose logging is more comprehensive\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should we add support for Docker buildx for multi-platform builds? (Future enhancement)\n2. Should we add image pull functionality for caching? (Out of scope)\n3. Should we implement credential helpers for secure registry auth? (Future enhancement)\n\n## References\n\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - Docker integration requirement\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` - DockerService class structure\n- AR-022 - BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime implementations\n- Docker Python SDK Documentation: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [67:13] Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [99:27] Type \"float\" is not assignable to declared type \"int\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py":[{"range":{"start":{"line":66,"character":12},"end":{"line":66,"character":36}},"message":"Argument of type \"float\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"str\"","severity":1,"code":"reportArgumentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportArgumentType"}},{"range":{"start":{"line":98,"character":26},"end":{"line":98,"character":30}},"message":"Type \"float\" is not assignable to declared type \"int\"\n  \"float\" is not assignable to \"int\"","severity":1,"code":"reportAssignmentType","source":"Pyright","codeDescription":{"href":"https://github.com/microsoft/pyright/blob/main/docs/configuration.md#reportAssignmentType"}}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870383976,"end":1775870383988}}}}
